==Old English==

===Etymology===
From Germaic ''*tagla-'', from Indo-European ''*dek-''.  Cognate with Middle Low German ''tagel'' ‘twisted whip’, Old High German [[zagal]] ‘animal’s tail’ (dialectical German [[Zagel]]), Old Norse [[tagl]] ‘horse’s or cow’s tail’, Gothic [[𐍄𐌰𐌲𐌻]] ‘hair of the head’; and, beyond Germanic, with Old Irish ''dūal'' ‘lock of hair’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'tæjel/

===Noun===
'''tæġel''' (''pl'' '''tæġlas''')
# a [[tail]]

